\begin_inset Formula $Z_{4}$
\end_inset

 and a subgroup of 
\begin_inset Formula $G$
\end_inset

.
 However, since the elements in the subgroup must be part of 
\begin_inset Formula $G$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $H$
\end_inset

 has four elements, 
\begin_inset Formula $Z_{4}=G$
\end_inset

