\begin_inset Formula $f(I)=I$
\end_inset

, the identity of 
\begin_inset Formula $G$
\end_inset

 is mapped to the identity of 
\begin_inset Formula $G'$
\end_inset

.
 A homomorphism becomes an isomorphism if the map is one-to-one and onto.
 
\end_layout

